CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 23, 1946, pg. 17 reads: "Going Up! - These smiles denote satisfaction as executives of The Pittsburgh Courier look at the 300,000th copy of The Courier which rolled off the press last week. Left to right: James M. Reid, news editor; W.P. Bayless, circulation manager; William G. Nunn, managing editor; Mrs. Robert L. Vann, treasurer, and Bud Waters, head pressman."
TitMainTitle: James Reid, W. B. Bayless wearing pinstriped suit, Bill Nunn Sr., and Jessie Vann watching Bud Waters writing on the 300,000th copy of the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper
